---SCHOOL PROVIDED MEALS---WEEKLY SIGN UP FORM

Leland CUSD #1 has a new food service company and will have a few changes to our meal program during this time of Remote Learning.

Please use this link for a form to sign up for Leland CUSD #1 provided breakfast and lunch meals. At this time meals will be free for any Leland Community member under the age of 18.

Meals will be served 'grab and go' style (or brown-bag style). When you sign up, you will be receiving all breakfasts & lunches for that week (this is not a daily program).

I will be sending out a new sign up form each Tuesday FOR THE FOLLOWING WEEK. The sign-up needs to be filled out no later than 3:00 that Wednesday. MEALS WILL BE DELIVERED/PICK UP on MONDAY & THURSDAY next week!!

School Meal Sign Up for week of Sept 14th.

Be sure to read the email with the attached link each week for any special notices.

The sign up form will be locked after 5:00pm Wednesday, 9/9/2020.

Leland Community Unit School District #1 is with Chris Bickel in Leland, Illinois.
August 22, 2014 at 3:14 PM · Leland, IL ·

The ALS Ice Bucket Challenge has hit Leland School.

Mrs. Frederick, Admin Asst, nominated our new Principal, Chris Bickel for the ALS challenge.

All the K-6 students and staff were each given a glass of water and class by class dumped water on Mr. Bickel's head.
What a great sport he was and the kids had a blast soaking their new Principal.

Great way to start the hot weekend!!

Your 2020-2021 Leland School Supply List is here!!

Thank you for being patient while we've been working on what our 2020-2021 school year will look like. Remember, like everything else this year this list is not definitive. For families participting in the 100% Remote Learning option, use your best judgement for the supplies you will need. Student schedules for grades 5-12 should be visible on Teacher Ease now to help you select your supplies.

We are excited to get students back in our building, we've missed you all!

Wishing you good health and a safe Return to Learn!!! Enjoy supply shopping and the waning summer days. Remember: Excellence Has No Finish Line, so let's do this!! #achieveexcellencetogether #pantherpride

post_text: With all of the uncertainties facing us for the fall, the District is working very hard on coming up with a re-opening plan. During this time we have been holding off on "publishing" school supply lists. Please know the staff and teachers at Leland School are altering and adapting with each new update. Notably, it's the time of year when people are definitely asking about school supply lists. We hope to have those lists out to you in the next couple weeks. While we do not have grade-specific items to date, you might consider general supplies that would work with in-person instruction, as well as remote learning instruction. Thank you for your patience as we try to come up with the best scenario for the families in our district!
text: With all of the uncertainties facing us for the fall, the District is working very hard on coming up with a re-opening plan. During this time we have been holding off on "publishing" school supply lists. Please know the staff and teachers at Leland School are altering and adapting with each new update. Notably, it's the time of year when people are definitely asking about school supply lists. We hope to have those lists out to you in the next couple weeks. While we do not have grade-specific items to date, you might consider general supplies that would work with in-person instruction, as well as remote learning instruction. Thank you for your patience as we try to come up with the best scenario for the families in our district!

post_text: Thank you to the district families and staff that took part in our Return to School survey. Administration is reviewing all of the responses given. Along with ISBE, RoE, IDPH, and CDC guidelines, we will take your responses into consideration as we work to develop a plan that's safe, yet provides optimal educational experiences for the students and staff of Leland CUSD #1. With all of the uncertainties facing us, one thing remains constant and that is that things continue to change! We are working to create a plan for the 2020-2021 school year. As always, we will do our best to get that information out as quickly as we can, but please be patient as we continue our journey through this unchartered territory.

**6/1: Updated information regarding the playground area at Leland School.**
Please read the attached message from Mrs. Moore:
"Leland is in Region 2, which has entered Phase 3 of the reopening guidelines for Illinois. Because this includes parks and outdoor activities permitted for up to 10 people practicing social distancing, I mistakenly made the choice to post that our playground would be open. However, Governor Pritzker has specifically mandated that playgrounds remain closed until Phase 4. My apologies, and I want to take this opportunity to thank everyone for your understanding and compliance as we work together to follow the recommendations and guidelines for our shared health and safety."
Please stay tuned for updates as they become available.

post_text: The “stay away” signs have been taken down from the school playground and ball field areas! However, please use common sense and your best judgement before using the equipment, if you are sick or have been recently exposed to someone that’s been running a fever or showing any other symptoms of illness, please do not use the equipment. You should still be following the recommended guidelines from the IDPH. As always, with our playground being on school property weapons, tobacco/other drugs, and alcohol are not allowed at any time! Please use care and respect on our grounds!

post_text:
Passing along a message from the Leland Youth Athletic Association regarding summer league ball:

Dear Athletes & Parents:
The LYAA knows how anxious everyone is to return to our normal way of life. We should be rounding bases and preparing for a fun summer of baseball, t-ball & softball. To be transparent, we want to let everyone know that we are holding out a bit longer for direction from the state and county. We might be optimistic, but we are just as uncertain of the future as anyone. The LEAGUES that our Leland teams are a part of have yet to cancel the overall season. So with that, we will wait a little longer as well to make that call.

We will post any information as soon as we know! THANK YOU for your support!🖤💚⚾️🥎🐾

post_text: Everyone needs to share a little of this young man’s optimism right about now! Billy S. says his “panther is shown with school books and a Leland Chromebook, because anyone can learn”...anywhere, any time. As long as we all just keep learning! My grandma, who was a 5th grade teacher for over 40 years always said to me, “it’s a day worth living if you learned something new”. Billy, you’re right on target, I’m proud of you! And please take note of this panther’s fantastic smile! Love it!

post_text:
Happy Easter from your friends and family at Leland CUSD 1. Hoping this finds you healthy and ready for new beginnings!

As a reminder if you have displayed Easter Eggs for our Socially Distant Egg Hunt, please be sure to email Mr. Bickel (cbickel@leland1.org) your address and how many you hung up.
* These need to be visible from the street! *Only eggs in town limits will be counted for the grand total. *Anyone is welcome to go on the hunt. *Feel free to tag us in your pics while you’re hunting. *A prize will be awarded to the family that has the correct number of eggs counted. * Email your guess to Mr. Bickel by 7:00pm tonight. *
This is meant to be a fun project for your whole family as a way to enjoy the holiday while still honoring social distancing guidelines. Please be safe, be well, have fun, and Happy Easter.

March 23 at 9:41 AM ·

LET'S HEAR IT FOR OUR GRADUATES

I know in the big scheme of things, this is NOT a big problem.

But, I would like to give a shout out to all the grade school, high school, and college students who might be missing out on graduation and many other milestones this spring.

My daughter is one of those kids, so I thought I would post some photos of her as a first grader and as a senior. Parents or graduates, feel free to post yours here or at WGN Morning News Facebook page and we will show them on the air this spring.

Remember, "If we don't mark the milestones, we're just passing the time." So true.

post_text:
Good evening Leland Panthers. I hope you are enjoying your “spring” break and all this white stuff we are being blessed with today. As a reminder, the school sack meal program begins tomorrow. We are still going to have pick up or delivery options available from 10am-noon. Please, as the governor has mandated, avoid social gatherings by only sending one person per family to pick up meals if you have selected the pick up option. It is best not to be traveling in groups especially to public places, and we really all need to do our part by following the Shelter-in-Place/Social Distancing order.
If you have not signed up for this free sack meal program, which includes breakfast and lunch items, and need these items for your Leland School students, please email Mrs. Niles (aniles@leland1.org) or Mrs. Bland (mbland@leland1.org) as soon as possible to ensure enough meals are packaged.
Thank you for your patience and flexibility during this constantly evolving crisis.

post_text: Shout out to Mrs. Hawk & Mr. Bland's BizInnovator Class...Al and Marcy Kinney gave the BizInnovator Class a great opportunity to try their hand at designing an ad campaign for their realtor business. The students learned what realtors do, how to design marketing questions to conduct an interview, and then how to take that information to customize an ad campaign. Last Friday they presented their designs and plans to the Kinney's and did a great job! They will now take the feedback to create necessary changes and additions for their clients. Thank you to the Kinneys for working with our students. It is relationships between school and community that make small schools so wonderful!! 💚🐾🖤

post_text:
Last week was our annual Middle School Science Fair. If you've never attended one, you should consider it next year! Our 6th-8th grade students work very hard beginning in the fall to get to the final display you see at the Fair. Students are in attendance to answer any questions regarding their experiment. The feeling of accomplishment is almost palpable on that final evening! Congratulations to ALL of our students! This year's winners recognized are:
Honorable Mention: Gunnar Swenson, Laynie Wold, Alex Vergara, Grace Ackerman
3rd place - Brooklynn Guelde; 2nd place - Brynn Pennnington;
1st place - The Effects of Recycled Water on Plants by Malayna Kinney. Our top 3 winners will represent Leland at the regional science fair at NIU this spring! Good luck to all!

I just sent out an emergency call system TEST via text message and voice call. When that call comes in, if you say hello the message should begin immediately. If you do not, the system automatically defaults to about a 6-second pause. Please listen to the entire message.

If you received the messages on all numbers you would like, you need to do nothing. If you would like to delete or add a number, please email aniles@leland1.org with any corrections. Also, if you would like TeacherEase updated with those numbers, please let us know that as well!

At this point, school is still in session for tomorrow.

If you have to go out tonight, please be safe & stay warm.

Last Friday, our elementary classes had an assembly to review and celebrate the COMMITMENT Character Counts trait that was the focus of January. Each month at the assembly, our 5th grade group prepares a contest or activity for the classes. This month the traveling trophy went to the 5th GRADE CLASS for winning charades! Additionally, we had some 3rd grade girls present a rap song about anti-bullying! Leland School has some pretty amazing young people! Congratulations to the following for earning the Excellence Award for Commitment:
K (Haag) - Edith S; K (Flewellin) - Ethan H; 1st - Evelyn S; 2nd - Kira H; 3rd - Isabella D; 4th - Kyler C; 5th - Joshua T.
A special shout out to the overall elementary student: Isabella Diaz!

January is School Board Recognition Month!

The LEA (Leland Education Association) put together this bulletin board to recognize the members of our local School Board of Education.

Our board members give of their time and effort in making sure that our students have amazing educational opportunities. Their families sacrifice time with them so that they can spend hours making important decisions for our school.

Thank you to Janet Plote, Claire Anderson, Brad Riskedal, Tage Shumway, Dan Todd, Heather Wesson, and Sara Miller!

post_text:
Thank you to all servicemen and women on this Veteran’s Day. A special shout out to Leland American Legion Post 570 for another amazing assembly. This year Mr. Bickel introduced some 3rd grade young ladies as they shared their acrostic poetry for VETERAN, Post Chaplain Bob Shumway shared a touching prayer, Post Commander Lance Brown taught us about the honor and integrity of the Table for One honoring all POW/MIA soldiers, Post 570 past and present Veterans’ names were read aloud, and our 5-12th students observed a beautiful, albeit frigid, tribute for all Veterans by Post 570 members.
.....with respect and gratitude- the Leland CUSD 1 family 💚🖤🇺🇸

post_text:
Next week is Red Ribbon Week already! This year’s national theme is: Send a Message. Stay Drug Free. Our High School group, S.A.D.D. (Students Against Destructive Decisions), is sponsoring Dress Up Days. The list did not get out before the end of school today. Please spread the word.

Monday = PJ Day (Just relax and make good choices)
Tuesday = Athlete Day (Team up against drugs!)
Wednesday = Super Hero Day (Be a hero, not a zero)
Thursday = COSTUME DAY (Happy Halloween)
Friday = Red Day (Pledge to “send” being safe)
text:
Next week is Red Ribbon Week already! This year’s national theme is: Send a Message. Stay Drug Free. Our High School group, S.A.D.D. (Students Against Destructive Decisions), is sponsoring Dress Up Days. The list did not get out before the end of school today. Please spread the word.

Monday = PJ Day (Just relax and make good choices)
Tuesday = Athlete Day (Team up against drugs!)
Wednesday = Super Hero Day (Be a hero, not a zero)
Thursday = COSTUME DAY (Happy Halloween)
Friday = Red Day (Pledge to “send” being safe)

post_text:
Leland School parents, some of you will be receiving "progress reports" in the next couple days. Here is the explanation:

The First Quarter of the school year was complete on Friday, 10/18/19. With our Middle School being on quarters for the 2019-2020 school year, and along with that, the change in first hour B-day courses for our 6th, 7th, & 8th grade students. Progress Reports will be coming home tomorrow, Tuesday, 10/22/19.

Progress Reports are simply a snapshot of grades on a specified date. The grades will continue into the 2nd quarter until a Report Card is run at the end of the semester.

You may log on to your parent portal at any time and see current grades. For this reason, the district will not be running progress reports for all grade levels. Report cards will be sent home after first semester.

Feel free to call the office if you have any questions.
